external_knowledge:
- "painting the heaviest shadow" metaphorically refers to the region with the highest number of death cases;
- This query emphasizes the impact of death cases within regions, focusing on the total count associated with each;
- The region with the most fatalities is metaphorically described as casting the darkest shadow.

sql:
SELECT hospital_name
FROM hospitals
WHERE hospital_id = 1 AND capacity > 150;

SELECT users.user_name, user_permissions.dataset_id, user_permissions.permission_level
FROM users
JOIN user_permissions ON users.user_id = user_permissions.user_id;

external_knowledge:
- Best performance in terms of case recovery refers to the highest average ratio of cases to recoveries.;
- Data entries refer to datasets.; 
- Regions with the same number of data entries are ranked by their case recovery performance.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM hospitals 
WHERE region_id = 1;

SELECT patient_id, hospital_id, case_id, admission_date, discharge_date, treatment_outcome
FROM patients
WHERE discharge_date > '2020-01-21' AND treatment_outcome = 'recovered';

SELECT province_state 
FROM regions 
WHERE (SELECT AVG(population) FROM regions) > 10000000;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_user_permissions
FROM user_permissions
WHERE permission_level = 'edit';
